1. Breakfast is one of the most skipped meals of the day. It is also one of the most harmful meals to miss as it helps regulate blood sugar levels and improves brain function.

2. Eating healthy at an early age will ensure that your child hits puberty at the correct age. Girls will find that their menstrual cycle is more regular with far lesser complications.

3. A well-balanced diet from an early age helps improve physical development. Many doctors argue that a healthy diet can help a child grow taller, have a better metabolism and can even improve their skin health.

4. Eating healthy from an early age will assist in building your child’s self-esteem and help regulate brain chemicals to fight off anxiety and depression
